arms.name: PF-04965842 Maintenance

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Age and Weight Requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subjects aged 12 years and over with a body weight 40 kg.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Atopic Dermatitis Diagnosis
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Moderate to severe atopic dermatitis as defined per the inclusion criteria (Appendix 2).

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Disease Severity
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Moderate to severe AD determined by pruritus NRS severity score on the day of baseline visit.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Chest X-ray Requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: A chest X-ray is required unless previously performed and documented within 12 weeks prior to Study Day 1.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Hypersensitivity Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Known hypersensitivity to PF-04965842 or any study drug excipients.

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Hepatitis B DNA Exclusion
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subjects who are hepatitis B surface antigen (HBsAg) negative, hepatitis B core antibody (HBcAb) positive, and hepatitis B surface antibody (HBsAb) positive at Screening who have HBV DNA above the lower limit of quantification (LLQ).

studyInterventions.name: PF-04965842
studyInterventions.description: An orally bioavailable small molecule that selectively inhibits JAK1 by blocking the ATP binding site.

studyInterventions.name: Placebo
studyInterventions.description: Matching placebo used in the double-blind maintenance treatment period.

studyInterventions.name: Topical therapy
studyInterventions.description: Topical therapy per local standard of care (SOC) used in combination with PF-04965842 during the rescue period.

studyInterventions.name: Acetylsalicylic acid
studyInterventions.description: Low dose (100 mg QD) permitted for cardiovascular prophylaxis.

studyInterventions.name: Topical corticosteroids (TCS)
studyInterventions.description: Must be washed out during the screening period.

studyInterventions.name: Topical calcineurin inhibitors (TCI)
studyInterventions.description: Must be washed out during the screening period.

amendments.name: Amendment 5
amendments.summary: The Columbia Suicide Severity Rating Scale (C-SSRS) will be administered to all ongoing subjects at all remaining scheduled visits in Run In and Blinded treatments, and Rescue weeks 0, 8, 12, 16, and up to and including the End of Treatment/Early Termination (EOT/ET) and/or the End of Study (EOS) visit to align with new cross-program processes.

amendments.name: Amendment 4
amendments.summary: For Taiwan only: Similar to China, other countries in Asia, such as Taiwan, have a high prevalence of hepatitis B surface antigen (HBsAg) negative, hepatitis B core antibody (HBcAb) positive, and hepatitis B surface antibody (HBsAb) positive serology. Therefore, Taiwan will adopt the same changes as those proposed for China in Amendment 3 to monitor the risk of hepatitis B reactivation.

amendments.name: Amendment 3
amendments.summary: The following changes, requested by an Ethics Committee in China for study B7451013, are being applied to the PF-04965842 program. These changes are in effect for China only: Subjects who are hepatitis B surface antigen (HBsAg) negative, hepatitis B core antibody (HBcAb) positive, and hepatitis B surface antibody (HBsAb) positive at Screening will have reflex testing for hepatitis B virus deoxyribonucleic acid (HBV DNA).

amendments.name: Amendment 2
amendments.summary: Updated Background and Rationale text to align across the JAK1 program; clarified the primary and secondary objectives and endpoints; addition of Key Secondary endpoint; clarified Study design and informed consent requirements; defined medicated topical therapy for clarity.

commentAnnotations.text: The Columbia Suicide Severity Rating Scale (C-SSRS) will be administered to all ongoing subjects at all remaining scheduled visits in Run In and Blinded treatments, and Rescue weeks 0, 8, 12, 16, and up to and including the EOT/ET and/or the EOS visit.
For Taiwan only: Similar to China, other countries in Asia, such as Taiwan, have a high prevalence of HBsAg negative, HBcAb positive, and HBsAb positive serology.
These changes are in effect for China only: Subjects who are HBsAg negative, HBcAb positive, and HBsAb positive at Screening will have reflex testing for HBV DNA.

studyAmendmentImpacts.description: Implementation of C-SSRS across all ongoing subjects and multiple study phases.
Removal of specific patient-reported outcome (PRO) endpoints.
Administrative changes and clarifications regarding dosing, PK sampling, and washout periods.
Implementation of Hepatitis B monitoring risk protocols for Taiwan.
Inclusion of reflex HBV DNA testing and longitudinal monitoring for specific serology profiles.

studyAmendmentReasons.reasonText: To align with new cross-program processes for suicide severity rating.
To align secondary objectives with the Statistical Analysis Plan.
High prevalence of specific Hepatitis B serology in Taiwan, requiring risk monitoring similar to China.
Requested by an Ethics Committee in China for study B7451013.
